We need two conda environments (e.g. decimer and molsnap)

Decimer Image Segmentation Installation
1. 
conda create -n decimer python=3.10
conda activate decimer
checkout the DECIMER Image Segmentation repository (https://github.com/Kohulan/DECIMER-Image-Segmentation/tree/master)
cd DECIMER-Image-Segmentation
conda install pip
python -m pip install -U pip
pip install .
pip install decimer-segmentation

2. Install dependencies for decimer-api (don't switch the conda environment)
Go to decimer-api/ directory
conda activate decimer
cd decimer-api 
pip install -r requirements.txt

3. Install dependencies for ML_model (go to the root folder)
cd KIDS25-Team6/
conda create -n molsnap python=3.10
conda activate molsnap
conda install pip
pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Install molsnap-api
cd molsnap-api/
conda activate molsnap
pip install -r requirements.txt

Now the installation is complete.
Run the decimer-api and molsnap-api

5. In a new terminal, cd into decimer-api 
cd decimer-api
uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8001 --reload

6. In a new terminal, cd into root directory (KIDS25-Team6)
cd KIDS25-Team6
uvicorn "molsnap-api.main:app" --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --reload

7. In a new terminal, cd into molsnap
cd molsnap

8. SKIP THIS IF YOU ALREADY HAVE NODE. Open new terminal (Node Installation)
We can install nvm, that will be easier. Follow installation guidelines here: http://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm

9. IF YOU HAVE NODE INSTALLED. Run this in your new terimal
cd molsnap
npm install
npm run dev

Now the web application should be ready on http://localhost:5173/




